e astrologers as idealized by the\nGreeks of the time, or they might have been non-existent (invented by a\nlatter-day Greek seeking omens for the birth of a great king), and they might\nhave arrived on 17 April 6 BC or months later, and they might or might not have\nbeen three in numbers with given names. But for the Star of Bethlehem alone,\nMolnar's astrological solution is convincing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2016 19:05:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-23"}
